  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This model has been applied in clinical research settings to evaluate hemolysis risk in centrifugal blood pumps. The CFD hemolysis prediction model for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump was assessed under ventricular assist device (VAD) operating conditions. Thirteen credibility factors were evaluated against Model Risk Level 5 requirements. Seven factors received formal assessment; six were flagged as epistemic gaps. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed. Despite gaps in individual factor achievement levels, the aggregate credibility posture was deemed sufficient for the intended low-stakes advisory use, and the assessment team accepted the package under the Minimal profile. No structured context of use object is bound to this unit; intended-use scope is conveyed only through this narrative.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-generic-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-experimental-hemolysis-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-cfd-mesh-dataset"
  ],
